'''Alfonsas Andriuškevičius''' (born November 18, 1940 in [[Vilkaviškis]], [[Lithuania]]<ref>{{cite encyclopedia|title=Andriuškevičius, Alfonsas |encyclopedia=Lietuva |volume=II |first=Ingrida |last=Korsakaitė |editor=Antanas Račys |page=69 |publisher=Mokslo ir enciklopedijų leidybos centras |year=2010 |isbn=978-5-420-01667-1|display-editors=etal}}</ref>) is a poet and art historian. He received the [[Recipients of the Lithuanian National Prize|Lithuanian National Prize]] in 2007 for essay ''Rašymas dūmais'' (''Writing with Smoke'', 2004) and collection of art critique ''Lietuvių dailė 1975-1995'' (''Lithuanian Art 1975-1995'', 1997).<ref>{{cite web|title=Įteiktos nacionalinės kultūros ir meno premijos |url=http://www.bernardinai.lt/index.php?url=articles/73993 |accessdate=2008-04-19 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080321233702/http://www.bernardinai.lt/index.php?url=articles%2F73993 |archivedate=21 March 2008 |deadurl=no |language=lt }}</ref>
Andriuškevičius graduated from [[Vilnius University]] in 1965, and went on to explore a variety of disciplines, including ethnography and philosophy. from 1974 to 1990 worked at [[Lithuanian Academy of Sciences]]. He taught the [[Russian language]], lectured at the [[Vilnius Academy of Art]] from 1989 to 2009. His publications include several books of art criticism, four poetry collections, and a collection of thirty essays.<ref>{{cite web|title=British Council Arts London Book Fair |url=http://www.britishcouncil.org/gr/arts-literature-iypy2006-lithuania.htm|accessdate=2008-04-19}}</ref>
== Selected works == * ''Rašymas dūmais'', 2004 * ''Grožis ir menas lietuvių estetikoje 1918–1940'', 1989 * ''33 eilėraščiai'', 1994 * ''66 eilėraščiai'', 1998 * ''Eilėraščiai'', 2000 * ''Lietuvių dailė 1975–1995'', 1997
