{{Infobox Organization | name = Django Girls | image = Djangogirls-logo.png | type = [[not-for-profit]] | key_people = {{plainlist| *Ola Sitarska *Ola Sendecka }} | website = {{URL|https://djangogirls.org}} }}
'''Django Girls''' is an international non-profit organization started by two Polish women, Ola Sitarska and Ola Sendecka,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.marieclaire.co.uk/life/16-women-doing-amazing-things-in-2016-14919|title=16 Women Doing Amazing Things in 2016|last=Proudfoot|first=Jenny|date=8 March 2016|work=Marie Claire|access-date=9 July 2017|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|language=en-US}}</ref> to inspire women from all backgrounds<ref name="rapidgrowth">{{Cite news|url=http://www.rapidgrowthmedia.com/innovationnews/022417-Django-Girls.aspx|title=Falling in love with programming: Django Girls inspires women to join the tech world|work=Rapid Growth|access-date=9 July 2017}}</ref> to get interested in technology and to become programmers,<ref>{{cite web|last1=Dillon|first1=Karen|title=Lawrence-born Django, which revolutionized website construction, celebrating its 10th anniversary|url=http://www2.ljworld.com/news/2015/jul/09/happy-birthday-django/|website=Lawrence Journal-world|access-date=17 June 2017}}</ref> offering a safe and friendly environment.<ref name="techspark">{{Cite web|url=https://techspark.co/django-girls-coming-cardiff-help-women-get-coding/|title=Django Girls is coming to Cardiff to help women get into coding -TechSPARK.co|website=techspark.co|language=en|access-date=9 July 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vam.ac.uk/articles/django-girls|title=V&A · Django Girls – Tech activists|website=Victoria and Albert Museum|language=en|access-date=9 July 2017}}</ref> It is known for the free workshops it hosts to help women to learn to program<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.onenewspage.com/video/20170425/7355456/Django-Girls-teaches-women-to-progam.htm|title=Django Girls teaches women to progam <nowiki>[sic]</nowiki>|work=One News Page|access-date=9 July 2017}}</ref> and for its [[Django (web framework)|Django]] tutorial.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Chilabert|first1=Hernán|title=Django Tutorials and Courses|url=https://hackr.io/tutorials/learn-django|website=hackr.io|accessdate=17 June 2017}}</ref> It is often supported by the [[Python Software Foundation]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Sushinsky|first1=Mary Ann|title=PSF supports more Django Girls!|url=https://pyfound.blogspot.com.br/2015/04/psf-supports-more-django-girls.html|website=Python Software Foundation News|access-date=17 June 2017}}</ref>
== History == The first Django Girls workshop, which kicked off Django Girls, happened during EuroPython 2014, in [[Berlin]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=2015 Team|first1=EuroPython|title=Our next keynote: Ola & Ola (Django Girls)|url=http://blog.europython.eu/post/117337312602/our-next-keynote-ola-ola-django-girls|website=EuroPython Blog|accessdate=17 June 2017}}</ref> Ola Sitarska and Ola Sendecka decided to use Django and Python because both are open source code platforms and not subject to copyright, which may help women developing their own ideas.<ref name="kathimerini">{{Cite news|url=http://www.ekathimerini.com/168766/article/ekathimerini/community/django-girls-make-the-male-dominated-world-of-it-more-accessible-to-women|title=Django Girls make the male-dominated world of IT more accessible to women, By Matthaios Tsimitakis {{!}} Kathimerini|access-date=2017-07-09|language=en}}</ref> Since then, the initiative has spread worldwide,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www2.ljworld.com/news/2015/jul/09/happy-birthday-django/|title=Lawrence-born Django, which revolutionized website construction, celebrating its 10th anniversary|website=LJWorld.com|language=en|access-date=2017-07-09}}</ref> reaching countries like [[Argentina]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.diariopanorama.com/noticia/242196/invitan-al-taller-django-girls-santiago-estero|title=Invitan al taller "Django Girls" en Santiago del Estero - Diario Panorama|last=Panorama|first=Diario|website=www.diariopanorama.com|access-date=2017-07-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.frm.utn.edu.ar/webgraduados/index.php/1235-taller-django-girls-en-pycon-argentina-2015-mendoza|title=Taller Django Girls en PyCon Argentina 2015 - Mendoza|last=User|first=Super|website=www.frm.utn.edu.ar|language=es-es|access-date=2017-07-17}}</ref> [[Australia]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.startupdaily.net/2016/07/coding-workshop-django-girls/|title=European coding workshop Django Girls comes to Brisbane to teach women tech skills - Startup Daily|date=2016-07-04|work=Startup Daily|access-date=2017-07-09|language=en-US}}</ref> [[Bolivia]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://boliviaemprende.com/eventos/taller-django-girls-mujeres-podran-aprender-programar-gratis|title=Taller Django Girls: Mujeres podrán aprender a programar gratis|date=2015-08-21|work=Bolivia Emprende|access-date=2017-07-17|language=es-ES}}</ref> [[Brazil]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://idgnow.com.br/mobilidade/2016/02/15/django-girls-realiza-workshop-gratuito-de-programacao-no-brasil/|title=Django Girls realiza workshop gratuito de programação no Brasil - IDG Now!|date=2016-02-15|work=IDG Now!|access-date=2017-07-09|language=pt-br}}</ref> [[Colombia]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.elheraldo.co/entretenimiento/programacion-web-para-mujeres-en-barranquilla-366549|title=Programación web para mujeres en Barranquilla|date=2017-05-28|access-date=2017-07-10|work=El Heraldo|language=es-co}}</ref> [[Ecuador]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.elmercurio.com.ec/526210-mujeres-se-capacitan-en-programacion/|title=Mujeres se capacitan en programación|date=2016-05-01|work=Diario El Mercurio - Cuenca Ecuador|access-date=2017-07-17|language=es-ES}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://vistazo.com/seccion/tecnologia/taller-gratuito-de-programacion-para-mujeres-en-guayaquil|title=Taller gratuito de programación para mujeres en Guayaquil|date=2016-06-22|work=Vistazo|access-date=2017-07-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.eltiempo.com.ec/noticias/cuenca/2/409962/mujeres-reciben-un-taller-sobre-programacion|title=Mujeres reciben un taller sobre programación|last=Tiempo|first=El|date=2017-03-26|work=El Tiempo|access-date=2017-07-17|language=es}}</ref> [[Ghana]],<ref name="technovagh">{{Cite web|url=https://technovagh.com/2017/06/19/event-django-girls-workshop-ispace-foundation/|title=Event: Django Girls Workshop At iSpace Foundation|last=Kuuire|first=Joseph-Albert|date=2017-06-19|website=Tech Nova|access-date=2017-07-09}}</ref> [[Nigeria]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://te