== Tutorial == The tutorial, which teaches how to create and deploy a blog application using Django, is maintained and updated by the Django Girls community, using Github. As of May 2018, the Django Girls tutorial has been published online in 14 languages<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tutorial.djangogirls.org/|title=Choose a language · Django Girls Tutorial|last=DjangoGirls|website=tutorial.DjangoGirls.org|language=en|access-date=9 July 2017}}</ref> besides its original English version. As of May 2018, more than 1,000,000 users have visited its website.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://kcur.org/post/django-celebrates-10-years-web-development-lawrence|title=Django Celebrates 10 Years Of Web Development In Lawrence|last=Newill|first=Cody|access-date=9 July 2017|language=en}}</ref>
== Django Girls workshops == Using a manual provided by the organization,<ref name="techspark" /><ref name="kathimerini" /> Django Girls volunteers offer free<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.popwebdesign.net/popart_blog/en/2015/11/coding-and-women-where-to-learn-to-code-for-free/|title=Coding and women: Where to learn to code for free?|date=2015-11-16|work=PopArt Studio|access-date=2017-07-09|language=en-US}}</ref> one<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.spacecubed.com/en/blog/read/159874717/perth-web-girls-blurring-boundaries-and-beating-the-gender-bias|title=Perth Web Girls: Blurring Boundaries and Beating the Gender Bias|work=Spacecubed|access-date=2017-07-09|language=en}}</ref> or two days workshops in many cities of the world, usually held during weekends.<ref name="rapidgrowth" /> It is aimed at complete beginners, teaching about HTML, CSS, Python and Django.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Tysnicka|first1=Agata|title=Django Girls: How 10Clouds Helps Get More Women into IT|url=https://10clouds.com/blog/django-girls-how-to-get-more-women-into-it/|website=10Clouds|accessdate=17 June 2017}}</ref> As of May, 2018 414 cities across 90 countries<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.siliconrepublic.com/careers/django-girls-dublin-april-rte-coding-grace?google_editors_picks=true|title=First Irish Django Girls coding event taking place this April|last=Gorey|first=Colm|date=2016-03-18|work=Silicon Republic|access-date=2017-07-09|language=en-GB}}</ref> have hosted Django Girls workshops, with [[Accra]],<ref name="technovagh" /> [[Athens]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://windycitygreek.com/greek-girls-technology/|title=Greek Girls Pave the Technology Path|date=2015-11-04|work=WindyCity Greek|access-date=2017-07-09|language=en-US}}</ref> [[Florence]],<ref>{{cite web|last1=Corvino|first1=Nadia|title=Django Girls a Firenze: workshop di programmazione per donne e ragazze|url=http://www.softrevolutionzine.org/2017/django-girls-firenze/|website=Soft Revolutionzine|accessdate=17 June 2017}}</ref> [[Kathmandu]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://techlekh.com/django-girls-workshop/|title=Django Girls Workshop #3 Successfully Organized in Kathmandu {{!}} TechLekh|date=2016-10-10|work=TechLekh|access-date=2017-07-09|language=en-US}}</ref> [[Lagos]],<ref>{{cite web|last1=Adeleke|first1=David|title=Django Girls is coming to Lagos. Ready your laptops ladies|url=http://techcabal.com/2016/01/18/django-girls-is-coming-to-lagos-ready-your-laptops-ladies/|website=Techcabal|accessdate=17 June 2017}}</ref> [[Lahore]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.morenews.pk/django-girls-workshop-in-lahore-apply-before-20th-may/|title=Django Girls workshop to be held in Lahore; apply before 20th May - More News|date=2016-05-12|work=More News|access-date=2017-07-09|language=en-US}}</ref> [[Oxford]],<ref>{{cite web|last1=Keown|first1=Callum|title=Coding event gets more Oxford women into computer programming|url=http://www.oxfordmail.co.uk/news/15286291.Coding_event_gets_more_Oxford_women_into_computer_programming/|website=Oxford Mail|accessdate=17 June 2017}}</ref> [[São José dos Campos]]<ref>{{cite web|last1=Kyoshy|first1=Felipe|title=Workshop promove inserção das mulheres na área de tecnologia|url=http://www.meon.com.br/noticias/regiao/workshop-promove-insercao-das-mulheres-na-area-de-tecnologia|website=Meon|accessdate=17 June 2017}}</ref> among them. As of May 2018, over 14,000 women have attended Django Girls workshops held across the globe.
